<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="NAME"><a class="permalink" href="#NAME">NAME</a></h1>
<code class="Nm">mdconfig</code> &#x2014;
<div class="Nd">configure MEMORY disks</div>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="SYNOPSIS"><a class="permalink" href="#SYNOPSIS">SYNOPSIS</a></h1>
<table class="Nm">
  <tr>
    <td><code class="Nm">mdconfig</code></td>
    <td><var class="Ar">special_file</var>
      <var class="Ar">512-byte-blocks</var></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="DESCRIPTION"><a class="permalink" href="#DESCRIPTION">DESCRIPTION</a></h1>
The <code class="Nm">mdconfig</code> command configures memory disk devices. It
  will associate the special file <var class="Ar">special_file</var> with a
  range of user-virtual memory allocated by the <code class="Nm">mdconfig</code>
  process itself. The <code class="Nm">mdconfig</code> command should be run in
  the background. If successful, the command will not return. Otherwise, an
  error message will be printed.
<p class="Pp">To &quot;unconfigure&quot; the memory disk, just kill the
    background <code class="Nm">mdconfig</code> process started earlier.</p>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="FILES"><a class="permalink" href="#FILES">FILES</a></h1>
<dl class="Bl-tag Bl-compact">
